HEADWORD: Quaggy
<hw>Quag"gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Quag</er>,
<er>Quagmire</er>.]</ety> <def>Of the nature of a quagmire; yielding or
trembling under the foot, as soft, wet earth; spongy; boggy.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧O'er the watery strath, or <xex>quaggy</xex> moss.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Collins.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Quagmire</ent>⟦br⟧
